author: jeremias
msg: Got a report about problems with JPEG images that have the "Adobe RGB" or "Adobe RGB (1998)" color profile. The image drifts into yellow when embedded natively in PDF. This revision adds a processing hint that ignores the embedded color profile which is better than getting the bad side-effect which is currently unexplained.
Extracted some JPEG processing helper code into a "JPEGFile" class.
